The paper deals with the construction of spanners, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and graph theory. The paper provides theoretical results on the performance of the greedy spanner construction, which is a well-studied algorithmic technique in these areas. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses the performance of spanners in doubling metrics, which is a topic in metric embeddings and geometric algorithms, suggesting cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of an approximate-greedy algorithm, which is a technique in optimization and information theory, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category as well.
